There was commotion yesterday in Ogwashi-Ukwu, Aniocha South LGA of Delta State, as an alleged reckless driver, name withheld ran into not less than seven persons, killing four instantly and injuring three. The accident happened as visitors were arriving the Mary Immaculate Catholic Church, Ogwashi-Ukwu venue of the funeral mass of Tony Iwelu, one of the aides to the Minister of Transport, Rt. Hon. Rotimi Amaechi’s, who was allegedly electrocuted in a hotel room recently. Eye witnesses said the young man whose mother was once a councilor in Aniocha South Local Government, must have been drunk or high with weed before taking over the wheels of a red camry car used in killing his victims. Sources alleged that the boy had been causing his parents trouble, and at a time was flown abroad to utilise a better opportunity in a sane environment but misused the opportunity and came back to continue in his gangsterism and waywardness. It was revealed that he even joined the vigilante group, which made him more violent than ever as he uses the platform to intimidate his victims and causing havoc in the community. Meanwhile, one of the victims included a family of four who were returning from church where they had gone to clean up ahead of today’s service. At the time of filing this report, victims have been evacuated to a mortuary in Ogwashi-Ukwu.